               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmra Māryām “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 2ra-117ra)&#xD; I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah and hymns (fols. 2ra-6vb)&#xD; I-2)
                     ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki ... “I worship Thee ...” (fols. 6vb-7vb)&#xD; I-3)
                     Introductory exhortation (fols. 7vb-9ra)&#xD; I-4) Taʾāmra Māryām: 100 miracles
                     (9rb-117ra)&#xD; I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾsi ... “Does not the man ...” (distributed
                     among the miracles of Mary, fols. 14va-49va)</summary>
                  
                  
                  
